titleStmt.title: Heads presented by the army to the Kings Most Excellent Majestie, on Saturday, June the 19. 1647.

notesStmt.note: With engraving of royal seal at head of document.

Called spurious by "A declaration of his Excellency Sir Thomas Fairfax, and the councell of warre" (Wing F143) and "A vindication of the army under the command of his excellency Sir Thomas Fairfax" (Wing V499).
Reproduction of the original in the British Library.
